The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 February is 200,765 (23,139.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 January, there were 11,202 new confirmed cases (1,291.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 January, there were 9,536 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 17% (1,666 extra cases).
